      "description": "This 997-generation Carrera S represents a pinnacle of analog feedback and mechanical harmony. Power is delivered via a 3.8L naturally aspirated flat-six featuring VarioCam Plus and an optimized intake manifold, producing a linear torque curve and a visceral 7,200 RPM redline. The Getrag six-speed manual gearbox offers crisp, short-throw engagement, paired with a factory-optioned limited-slip differential for surgical power distribution. The chassis remains in concours-level condition, featuring Porsche Active Suspension Management (PASM) and Monoblock four-piston calipers that retain their factory-fresh bite. Every bushing, seal, and heat shield is within original tolerances, ensuring the structural integrity and aerodynamic efficiency intended by Stuttgart. This is a collector-grade example with zero deferred maintenance and an unblemished undercarriage.",
